# Adapters Layer (`packages/adapters`)

- Implement repository interfaces; hide PostgreSQL, pgvector, Neo4j, Redis details
- All SQL and Cypher statements parameterized — no string interpolation of user input
- Celery calls behind `TaskDispatcher` adapter
- Vector records store embedding model, dimension, content hash, created time
- Never mix incompatible embedding spaces in one index

## Neo4j

Only the graph projector adapter writes to Neo4j. `GraphRepository` exposes bounded traversal only.

## Idempotency

Background task handlers must be safe to retry on identical inputs.
